00:00:33.940 --> 00:00:38.560
with the Federal Bureau of
Investigation as a special agent.

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:41.890
Over the years the FBI assigned
him to a myriad of postings

00:00:41.890 --> 00:00:46.820
in San Francisco, Chicago,
Denver, Mexico City, Los Angeles,

00:00:46.820 --> 00:00:51.220
Washington, D.C. and
Montevideo, Uruguay.

00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:54.650
He worked cases involving white
collar crime, domestic terrorism,

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:57.450
narcotics, foreign
counter intelligence

00:00:57.450 --> 00:01:00.030
and undercover assignments.

00:01:00.030 --> 00:01:04.620
He worked on the Patricia Hearst
Kidnapping, the Black Panther Party

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:08.690
and the FALN, a Puerto
Rican terrorist group.

00:01:08.690 --> 00:01:13.500
In Mexico he was the FBI case agent
and supervisor to the kidnapping

00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:18.150
and murder of DEA agent
Enrique Kiki Camarena.

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:20.780
His last assignment was
supervising, coordinating

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:25.840
and authorizing oversea
drug cases with the DEA.

00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:31.270
He joined lead plaintiff Mat Perez
and 310 other Hispanic agents

00:01:31.270 --> 00:01:33.360
in filing a class action lawsuit

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:36.030
on employee discrimination
against the FBI.

00:01:36.030 --> 00:01:41.220
The lawsuit was not about
hatred or bigotry, but subtle

00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:45.500
and unintentional discrimination
which became evil

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:47.100
when management retaliated

00:01:47.100 --> 00:01:51.560
against those investigative agents
it relied on for its success.

00:01:51.560 --> 00:01:54.080
The court-ordered systems
implemented

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:58.610
after the trial benefited the
FBI with greater opportunities

00:01:58.610 --> 00:02:03.200 position:56%
for all agents, developed
transparency and promotion policies,

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:08.220
and caused the FBI to promote
women at an unprecedented rate.

00:02:08.220 --> 00:02:16.080
He is the author of Systemic Evil:
Mat Perez v. the FBI and he plans

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:19.600
to write books on a
less serious subjects.

00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:21.430
